[Title]     GNU Ncurses

[Description]
GNU Ncurses is a library which provides capabilities to write text to a terminal in a 
terminal-independent manner. It supports pads and color as well as multiple highlights and forms
characters. It is typically used to implement user interfaces for command-line applications. The
accompanying ncursesw library provides wide character support.

[Home]      https://www.gnu.org/software/ncurses/

[Class]     Core | Gnu
[Name]      ncurses
[Version]   6.1

